proaches the topic of clean torture - which has been used for decades in prison camps as a defense strategy by democracies - through the lenses of Media and Cultural Studies. With a model of analytical theatricality, she lays bare the destructive-performative mechanisms of practices of torture, which are invisible and unspeakable - on the body, in language, in discourse. A work on the impossible, which seeks after the disappearing and says the unsayable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aCultural Studies. 4aDemokratie. 4aGewalt. 4aKultur. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aPerformativität. 4aTheater. 4aTheaterwissenschaft. 4aTheatralität. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCultural Theory.  aCulture.  aDemocracy.  aMedia.  aPerformativity.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.  aTheatricality.  aViolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2015z9783110438741oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839431573zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839431573423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839431573/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DSWb2015  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016